        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 3:42PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 342 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sugar Grove, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rural Retreat...
Sugar Grove...
Mount Rogers National Recreation Area...
Atkins...
and Marion Wytheville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
